BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:E9AJhxEYddKRtwgxHM1Jb
SUMMARY:First Thursday - March
DTSTAMP:20260306T004548Z
DTSTART:20260305T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Visit MOHAI on the First Thursday of every month for free admis
	sion to the museum’s permanent exhibits between 5—8 pm.  \\nFree admission
	 includes access to all of MOHAI’s award winning exhibits\\\, including ou
	r temporary display Riding Together: 135 Years of Cycling in Seattle\\\, a
	nd special exhibit Kickstands Up! 125 Years of Motorcycling in the PNW. Ad
	vance online tickets are not required\\\, but may be reserved below. \\nTh
	is evening only\\\, you can also join a Bicycle Repair Workshop with Bike 
	Works! See more information and register for the 5:30 Session or the 6:45 
	Session.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/first-thursday-march/\n\nFrom MOHAI - 
	Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/first-thursday-march/
LOCATION:MOHAI\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\,
	 United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:GKwndQ-M82Se7JCYG86Bs
SUMMARY:Bicycle Repair Workshop with Bike Works
DTSTAMP:20260306T004548Z
DTSTART:20260305T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:This event has sold out\\nAspiring and experienced cyclists ali
	ke agree that life is better when your bike works. This is why representat
	ives from Bike Works will be onsite during Free First Thursday to teach tw
	o hour-long bicycle repair workshops. Learn the basics that will keep you 
	safely riding after the rubber meets the road. While you’re at the museum\
	\\, get a crash course in Seattle cycling history from MOHAI’s exhibit\\\,
	 Riding Together: 135 Years of Cycling in Seattle. \\nThese workshops are 
	offered for free and require registration\\\, as space is limited. For acc
	essibility support\\\, general inquiries\\\, or to be added to a wait list
	 please email programs@mohai.org.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/bicycle-repai
	r-workshop-with-bike-works/2026-03-05/1/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History
	 & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/bicycle-repair-workshop-with-bike-works/2026-03
	-05/1/
LOCATION:Microsoft Lakefront Pavilion\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seatt
	le\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
