BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3Yqd5TEGhvtP7gTXefZTE
SUMMARY:History Café: Seattle Mystic Al Hubbard
DTSTAMP:20260306T004548Z
DTSTART:20260318T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Brad Holden\\\, author of Seattle Mystic Alfred M. Hubbard
	 for a discussion of one of Seattle’s most mysterious figures. Hubbard fir
	st appeared in the papers in 1919 for his supposed invention of a perpetua
	l motion machine that harnessed energy from Earth’s atmosphere. From there
	\\\, he transformed himself into a bootlegger\\\, radio pioneer\\\, top-se
	cret spy\\\, and eventually “the Johnny Appleseed of LSD”. \\nHistory Café
	 is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink and MOHAI. \\nASL Interp
	retation and CART captioning are available during the program. In addition
	\\\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are available upon re
	quest. For more accessibility support\\\, email programs@mohai.org two wee
	ks before the program. \\nGrab some food for thought–light food and drink 
	will be available to purchase in the atrium. \\nIf you can’t make it to th
	e museum\\\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend
	 this event.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-seattle-mystic-al-hub
	bard/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-seattle-mystic-al-hubbard/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
